# tui/ code feedback

## Strengths
- Tidy, small, idiomatic. Each file has one responsibility, functions
  stay short. Matches the "feather" goal in AGENTS.md.
- Good use of stack-allocated fixed buffers (`var fixedBuf [256]byte`
  in `statusBarView`) and `strconv.AppendInt` instead of `fmt.Sprintf`
  — respects the no-`Sprintf` rule.
- Clean `Mode` enum, single `Model`, `Message` shape. Debug helpers
  neatly isolated in `debug.go`.
- Layout is described in a comment next to its functions — matches
  "comments beside implementation" rule.
- Layout now derived from `inputHeight`/`statusBarHeight` constants,
  so multi-line input growth is a one-line change.
- Persistent render buffers on `Model` (`screen`/`blank`/
  `inputScratch`) reused across frames — keystrokes are
  allocation-free in the common case.
- Row-level dirty mask (`dirtyRows`) — only changed rows are
  rewritten; cursor-only moves skip `Render` entirely.
- Scrolling via `Model.Scroll` + PageUp/PageDown; `NewView` clamps
  to the valid viewport, `handleEnter` snaps to latest.
- `Render` clears stale bytes with `ESC[K` (skips status row so
  the embedded cyan fill survives).

## Issues / smells
1. `input.go:98` `handleCtrl` only handles Ctrl-H/Backspace/Enter/
   Ctrl-J. Ctrl-C is handled in `HandleInput` as `KindQuit`, Ctrl-D
   returns via `KindEOF` — neither logs before exit except `KindQuit`
   prints `"CtrlC"`. Inconsistent.
2. `model.go:36` — `ModelName: "DeepSeek v4 (Pro)"` hardcoded; no
   config injection despite AGENTS.md mentioning swappable offline
   models (Qwen/DeepSeek). Should come from config.
3. `input.go:109` `handleCSI` only handles Left/Right/PageUp/
   PageDown; up/down/Home/End/Delete are silently logged-and-dropped.
   At least `Home`/`End` trivial given current `buf`.
4. `view.go:97-101` — Each displayed message still allocates one
   `[]byte(Text[:clamp])` per frame. Bounded by `chatAreaRows` (~22)
   so not urgent; pool into a `msgScratch [][]byte` when this
   matters.
5. `model.go` `NewModel` still embeds the DEBUG 100-message seed.
   Remove once real agent output is wired in.
6. `input.go` `HandleLine(ch byte)` operates on bytes, so UTF-8
   sequences typed in raw mode are split into bytes and the
   terminal may render garbage. Needs rune reconstruction before
   multi-line input work begins.

## Architectural gaps
- No streaming output / spinners for `ModeLoading` and
  `ModeStreaming`.
- No theming hook (AGENTS.md lists Theming as a goal); ANSI color
  codes are inlined in `statusBarView`.
- No tests.

# What to implement right now (priority order)

1. **Hardcode removal** — pass `ModelName` and status text in from
   config/main, not `NewModel`. Also removes the DEBUG seed block.
2. **Theming stub** — `type Theme struct{ StatusBarBg, StatusBarFg
   [3]byte }`, pass into `statusBarView`. Replaces raw
   `\033[38;2;0;0;0m\033[48;2;0;180;244m` literal.
3. **`Home`/`End`/`Delete` CSI** in `handleCSI` — trivial given
   existing cursor logic.

Closed in this pass:
- Bounds & safety guard in `NewView` (TermRows<2 / TermCols<1) —
  no more `screenBuf[-1]` panic.
- `fillLine(..., '.')` debug dots replaced with spaces.
- `HandleEnter` now appends to `Messages` before clearing `buf`.
- Content area renders the last `chatAreaRows` messages bottom-up.
- `[]byte(Text[:clamp])` panic fixed via `min(TermCols, len(Text))`.
- Shadowed `len` variable renamed to `nMsg`.
- Layout derived from `inputHeight`/`statusBarHeight` constants via
  `chatAreaRows` / `inputRow` / `statusBarRow` — ready for
  multi-line input growth.
- Empty-input guard on Enter (skips blank sends).
- Persistent `screen` / `blank` / `inputScratch` buffers on `Model`
  — keypoints are allocation-free (only `[]byte(Text[:clamp])` per
  visible message remains).
- Row-level `dirtyRows` mask + `markRowDirty` / `markAllDirty`
  helpers — `Render` writes only dirty rows and clears the bits.
  Cursor-only moves (`handleLeft`/`handleRight`) skip `Render`
  entirely and just reposition via `MoveCursorTo`. `handleBackspace`
  skips when `buf` didn't shrink.
- `pollResize` clamps `cursorX` to `len(buf)` first, then to
  `cols-1` — cursor can no longer float past content on shrink.
- `Input.cursorY` comment is now honest: reserved for future
  soft-wrap, always 0 today.
- `HandleLine` caps at `cols` (NOTE marks future soft-wrap spot);
  no more offscreen cursor drift.
- `Model.Scroll` + `pageUpShift`/`pageDownShift`; `NewView` clamps
  to `[0, max(0, nMsg-chatAreaRows)]`, `handleEnter` snaps to
  latest.
- `Render` emits `ESC[K` after each row to wipe stale bytes;
  skips the status row so the embedded cyan fill survives.
- DEBUG seed of 100 messages in `NewModel` for scroll testing.
- `dbgInput`/`dbgModel` gated by `//go:build debug` tag — release
  builds pull no `log` import and emit no debug output. Build
  with `go build -tags debug`.
- Status bar cols x rows display gated by a `Model.Debug` runtime
  flag — off by default, no per-keystroke `AppendInt` cost in
  normal use.
- Rune-aware truncation: `runeWidth` + `truncateToCols` in
  `width.go` (no external dep — covers East Asian widths, emoji,
  combining marks). `messagesToBuf` slices by byte-offset-on-
  rune-boundary, so Italian accents and emoji never render as
  broken bytes. A wide rune that doesn't fit is dropped wholesale
  rather than split.